Pain in the left hip - time to see the physio again
Hill session with club in styal woods.Time estimated as watch playing up.
New PB, beat target time (20.30) by 17 seconds
2 x 4 Hills at Quarry Bank Mill Styal - seperated by a break of approx. 5 minutes - with club
Ran for 35.0 minutes then had to wallk for approximately 4 minutes due to extreme dizziness, followed by 10 minute jog home as not feeling too great.
Hill session with club at Styal Mill 3 sets of 2 reps (rests following each set were 3:23, 3:06 and 5.19 respectively)Around car park, down steps, around pond, up hill
Run with club, 2 x 2.5 miles seperated by 4 minute rest
2 sets of 3 hills - each hill rep followed by a recovery loop (2 minutes rest between sets)
Gaelic football - skills, drills and half-pitch game
Easy run through Styal woods - estimated distance

3 x 3 hill loops of 1.25 miles at Quarry Bank Mill with club with one extra loop to finish. Each set of three seperated by approximately 4 minutes of rest. Went over on right ankle during the 9th loop!
New PB - disappointed with split between 8 and 9km, not sure what happened!
Run with club, probably a bit too much too soon after Sunday's race - my legs are in pieces!
Club run - fast finish. About 8 minutes rest during the run waiting for others to catch up (not included in time).
Hill session at Styal mill with club (2 sets of 3 loops - each loop 0.65km). 4 minute rest between sets. Last run until November!
Fell over and bumped head after approximately 9 km. Slow last 2 - 3km.
First run since fracturing arm on the 3rd of May.
Approx time. Easy first 8 km followed by fast 2km finish.
Right caf started hurting approx 30 minutes into run.
Approx distance and time. Easy run - very painful calf (right leg).
